    "guides.vedicAstrology.tldrContent": "Vedic Astrology (Jyotish) is an ancient Indian system using the sidereal zodiac, 27 Nakshatras, and 9 planets to analyze birth charts (Kundli). Unlike Western astrology, it emphasizes the Moon sign and uses unique predictive systems like Vimshottari Dasha. Key components include 12 houses representing life areas, planetary strengths/weaknesses, and remedial measures for challenging placements.",
