    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.q1": "What is Vedic Astrology?",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.a1": "Vedic Astrology, also known as Jyotish Shastra, is an ancient Indian system of astrology that originated over 5,000 years ago. It uses the sidereal zodiac (based on fixed star positions) and incorporates unique concepts like Nakshatras (lunar mansions), Dashas (planetary periods), and detailed divisional charts to provide comprehensive life predictions.",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.q2": "How is Vedic Astrology different from Western Astrology?",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.a2": "The main differences are: 1) Vedic uses the sidereal zodiac while Western uses tropical zodiac (about 24 degrees difference), 2) Vedic emphasizes the Moon sign while Western focuses on Sun sign, 3) Vedic uses 27 Nakshatras for detailed analysis, 4) Vedic has unique predictive systems like Vimshottari Dasha, and 5) Vedic astrology is more deterministic with emphasis on karma and remedies.",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.q3": "What is a Kundli or Birth Chart?",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.a3": "A Kundli (also called Janam Kundli or birth chart) is a map of the sky at the exact moment and location of your birth. It shows the positions of all planets in the 12 houses and zodiac signs. This chart serves as the foundation for all astrological predictions and analysis in Vedic astrology.",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.q4": "What are Nakshatras?",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.a4": "Nakshatras are 27 lunar mansions or star constellations that the Moon passes through during its monthly cycle. Each Nakshatra spans 13°20' of the zodiac and has unique characteristics, ruling deity, and planetary lord. Your birth Nakshatra (based on Moon's position) reveals deep insights about your personality, nature, and life path.",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.q5": "What is a Dasha in Vedic Astrology?",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.a5": "Dasha is a planetary period system unique to Vedic astrology. The most commonly used is Vimshottari Dasha, a 120-year cycle where each planet rules for a specific period. The sequence is: Ketu (7 years), Venus (20), Sun (6), Moon (10), Mars (7), Rahu (18), Jupiter (16), Saturn (19), Mercury (17). Your current Dasha significantly influences life events and experiences.",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.q6": "Can Vedic Astrology predict the future accurately?",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.a6": "Vedic astrology provides tendencies and probabilities rather than fixed outcomes. It shows the karmic patterns and potential life events based on planetary positions. While skilled astrologers can make remarkably accurate predictions, free will and personal choices also play a significant role. Remedies can help modify challenging planetary influences.",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.q7": "What are Doshas in Vedic Astrology?",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.a7": "Doshas are specific planetary combinations or placements that can create challenges in certain life areas. Common doshas include Mangal Dosha (Mars affliction affecting marriage), Kaal Sarp Dosha (all planets between Rahu-Ketu), Pitra Dosha (ancestral karma issues), and Sade Sati (Saturn's 7.5-year transit over Moon). Each dosha has specific remedies to mitigate its effects.",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.q8": "How can I learn Vedic Astrology?",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.faq.a8": "Start by understanding the basics: zodiac signs, planets, houses, and Nakshatras. Generate your own birth chart and study it. Read classical texts like Brihat Parashara Hora Shastra. Practice analyzing charts of people you know. Consider taking courses from reputable teachers. Most importantly, be patient - mastering Vedic astrology takes years of dedicated study and practice.",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.tldr.title": "TL;DR - Quick Summary",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.tldr.content": "Vedic Astrology (Jyotish) is an ancient Indian system using the sidereal zodiac, 27 Nakshatras, and 9 planets to analyze birth charts (Kundli). Unlike Western astrology, it emphasizes the Moon sign and uses unique predictive systems like Vimshottari Dasha. Key components include 12 houses representing life areas, planetary strengths/weaknesses, and remedial measures for challenging placements.",
    "guides.vedicAstrology.tableOfContents": "Table of Contents",
