    "doshas.mangalDosh.faq.1.question": "What percentage of people have Mangal Dosha?",
    "doshas.mangalDosh.faq.1.answer": "Approximately 40-50% of people have some form of Mangal Dosha. However, the severity varies greatly. Only about 10-15% have severe Mangal Dosha that requires remedies. Many cases are mild and get cancelled by other planetary positions.",
    "doshas.mangalDosh.faq.2.question": "Can a Manglik marry a non-Manglik?",
    "doshas.mangalDosh.faq.2.answer": "Yes, a Manglik can marry a non-Manglik after performing appropriate remedies. Kumbh Vivah (symbolic marriage to a pot, banana tree, or Peepal tree) is commonly performed before the actual marriage. Additionally, if the Mangal Dosha is cancelled by other factors in the chart, marriage can proceed without remedies.",
    "doshas.mangalDosh.faq.3.question": "Does Mangal Dosha reduce after age 28?",
    "doshas.mangalDosh.faq.3.answer": "Yes, according to many astrologers, the intensity of Mangal Dosha significantly reduces after age 28. Mars matures around this age, and its malefic effects become less pronounced. However, this doesn't mean the dosha completely disappears. The reduction depends on the overall chart and other planetary positions.",
    "doshas.mangalDosh.faq.4.question": "Which house placement of Mars is most severe?",
    "doshas.mangalDosh.faq.4.answer": "Mars in the 7th house is considered the most severe placement for Mangal Dosha as it directly affects the house of marriage and partnerships. The 8th house placement is also very challenging as it affects longevity and can cause sudden events. The 1st house placement affects personality and can make the person aggressive in relationships.",
    "doshas.mangalDosh.faq.5.question": "How long does it take for remedies to show effect?",
    "doshas.mangalDosh.faq.5.answer": "The time for remedies to show effect varies based on the severity of the dosha and consistency of practice. Generally, regular practice of mantras and lifestyle changes can show subtle improvements within 40-90 days. Major pujas and rituals may show effects within 6 months to 1 year. Consistency and faith are key factors in the effectiveness of remedies.",
    "doshas.mangalDosh.importantNote.title": "Important Note About Mangal Dosh",
    "doshas.mangalDosh.importantNote.content": "Mangal Dosha should not be a cause for excessive worry. Modern astrologers emphasize that this dosha is often overemphasized and many cancellation conditions exist. A proper analysis by a qualified astrologer considering the entire birth chart is essential before concluding about the presence and severity of Mangal Dosha. Many successful marriages exist where one or both partners have Mangal Dosha.",
    "doshas.mangalDosh.whatIs.title": "What is Mangal Dosh?",
    "doshas.mangalDosh.whatIs.content": "Mangal Dosha (also known as Manglik Dosha, Kuja Dosha, or Bhom Dosha) is an astrological condition that occurs when Mars (Mangal) is placed in the 1st, 2nd, 4th, 7th, 8th, or 12th house from the Ascendant (Lagna), Moon, or Venus in a birth chart. This placement is believed to create challenges in marriage and relationships.",
    "doshas.mangalDosh.effectsByHouse.title": "Effects by House Placement",
